comments.name: IN51Y
comments.text: H51Y is an uncommon nonpolymorphic accessory mutation selected in vitro by EVG, DTG, and CAB. Alone, it has minimal if any effect on INSTI susceptibility.

comments.name: IN230R
comments.text: S230R is a nonpolymorphic INSTI-selected mutation that primarily occurs in combination with other INSTI-resistance mutations. By itself, it appears to have minimal effect on susceptibility to available INSTIs.

comments.name: CABIntermediate
comments.text: This virus is predicted to have intermediate-level reduced susceptibility to CAB. The use of the combination of CAB/RPV should be considered to be contraindicated.

comments.name: DTGLow
comments.text: There is evidence for low-level DTG resistance. If DTG is used, it should be administered twice daily.
